resource "aws_s3_bucket" "data_bucket" {
  bucket = "company-data-bucket-2024"

  server_side_encryption_configuration {
    rule {
      apply_server_side_encryption_by_default {
        sse_algorithm     = "AES256"
      }
    }
  }

  tags = {
    Environment = "Production"
    Purpose     = "Data Storage"
  }
}
```
This corrected version of the Terraform script satisfies the policy requirement by enabling server-side encryption for the S3 bucket. The `server_side_encryption_configuration` block is added to the resource, and the `sse_algorithm` is set to "AES256" to ensure that the data is encrypted using the Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) with a 256-bit key.

The original infrastructure intent is preserved by maintaining the same bucket name and tags as in the original script. The corrected version also follows Terraform best practices by using the `server_side_encryption_configuration` block to enable server-side encryption, rather than relying on a separate `aws_s3_bucket_public_access_block` resource.
